100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 4, 1926, the United States government announced a new initiative to combat the rising tide of organized crime, with a focus on the prohibition of alcohol. In Europe, tensions escalated as France and Belgium prepared for potential military action against Germany over reparations disputes. Meanwhile, in the realm of science, the British explorer Sir Ernest Shackleton's Antarctic expedition garnered attention as it concluded with significant findings about the continent's geography.
